        public int insert(K k,
                  V v,
                  boolean dirty,
                  DataStore dataStore)
        Inserts a key, value pair into the set. This method uses NoDataStore(). Data may be lost during evict events. See insert(K, V, boolean, DataStore) Generally O(n) + D where m is slots, and D is time taken by datastore
        Parameters:
        k - key of the value being saved
        v - value of the key being saved
        dirty - wether this object needs to be written to the database.
        dataStore - for evicted data
